dfield St Clare, Suffolk, England",", , Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Avis","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and French: from the Middle English and Old French female personal name <i>Avice</i>, which may be from ancient Germanic <i>Aveza</i>, but more probably from Latin <i>Avitia</i> (also found in a masculine form, <i>Avitius</i>). In France, this surname is rare.","Portuguese and Spanish: habitational name from the little town of Avis (the stress is on the <i>i</i>) in Portalegre district (Portugal). This surname is found in the neighboring Spanish Extremadura.","Dutch: variant of <b>Aafjes</b> a metronymic from the female personal name <i>Ave</i>, which is of unclear origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Avins","meanings":["English: metronymic from the Middle English female personal name <i>Avine</i>, which is probably a pet form of   Avis  ."]},{"name":"Havis","meanings":["English: variant of   Avis   with prosthetic <i>H-</i>."]},{"name":"Avison","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): metronymic from the Middle English female personal name <i>Avice</i> (see   Avis  )."]},{"name":"Havice","meanings":["Perhaps an altered form of English   Avis  ."]},{"name":"Avon","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Avon (Wiltshire) or Little or Middle Avon (Gloucestershire), both named from the river on which they stand, or possibly a habitational name from a settlement on one of the rivers or small streams called Avon or Aven. These river names derive from the Celtic word for ‘river’, as reflected in Welsh <i>afon</i> and Gaelic <i>abhainn</i>. The modern surname is concentrated in Somerset and Wiltshire, England, suggesting it is associated chiefly with the Avon river that rises on the Gloucester-Wiltshire border and flows through Wiltshire and Somerset into the Severn.","from the Middle English female personal name <i>Avine</i>, which is probably a pet form of   Avis  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mr Thomas Avis was born about 1510, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Thomas Avis."},"et":{"Abt 1510–":"umbes 1510–Surnud","1510–Female":"1510–Surnud","1538–1638":"1538–1638","1510–Male":"1510–Surnud","1510":"1510","Abt 1510":"umbes 1510","1638":"1638","1538":"1538","Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, England":"Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, England",", , Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1510–":"noin 1510–Kuollut","1510–Female":"1510–Kuollut","1538–1638":"1538–1638","1510–Male":"1510–Kuollut","1510":"1510","Abt 1510":"noin 1510","1638":"1638","1538":"1538","Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, England":"Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, England",", , Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1510–":"environ 1510–Décédé","1510–Female":"1510–Décédée","1538–1638":"1538–1638","1510–Male":"1510–Décédé","1510":"1510","Abt 1510":"environ 1510","1638":"1638","1538":"1538","Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, England":"Bradfield St Clare, Suffolk, Angleterre",", , Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mr Thomas Avis est né environ 1510, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs Thomas Avis."},"de":{"Abt 1510–":"um 1510–Verstorben","1510–Female":"1510–Verstorben","1538–1638":"1538–1638","1510–